column5: I know yourself,Terry and I , would of sooner been on hard water with hut,s and hubs with heaters going, hot coffee, warm belly foods cooking on the heaters, constant fish catching, but when dealt with what we have, we got to make do.         Lets not be to hard on the guy that couldnt bring in the fish eh.   Thanks again buddy. Good to see ya boys.  Bring on the hard water.
Great to be on he water in Jan. Thanks guys
i chickened out yesterday too cold with that wind. good on ya guys for getting out.

i chickened out yesterday too cold with that wind. good on ya guys for getting out.  Yesterday was our day to go as well, but last minute we said not. At 5:30 this morning, the winds were very light out of the south west. They were still light when we launched. The wind switched back to west. The further out you were the more waves we had. Once we moved back into the bay, it was nice and an anchor ( I called sputnik) held us well.
Thanks for taking him off my hands Brian LOL
